section.section:
A child in step-down aftercare shall receive:
a step-down aftercare plan;
supervision by step-down aftercare staff in accordance with the step-down aftercare plan;
educational services; and
any other services necessary to implement the step-down aftercare plan.

text.section:
The step-down aftercare staff shall:
prepare a step-down aftercare plan for each child assigned to the step-down aftercare program and file the plan with the Department;
keep regular records concerning the progress of each child;
file with the Department a monthly progress report on each child; and
file with the Department an annual report on the outcome of step-down aftercare plans for the children in the step-down aftercare program, that includes to the extent possible:
information on the number of children who:
are rearrested;
are rearrested and charged with serious or violent offenses;
are rearrested and waived to the adult system;
are re-referred to the Department;
are readjudicated and recommitted;
graduate from high school or successfully complete a high school equivalency examination; and
are employed; and
other relevant information.
